node.text:
After the the struggles of the @usabmx GA nationals 
Kids asked to start “training”
Fun for me to be able to pass on a few decades of trial and error. The complaining brings back fun memories, I’ve never seen any individual at the highest levels of sport not complain 😂
It’s truly part of learning to suffer through it, the ones who are quiet seem to be the ones that just quit in my experience 🤷🏽‍♂️
I love their grind and never wanting to quit attitude 
Dads finally getting to give when asked and needed 🙌🏻😍

node.text: I am really proud to be part of Moto40 with these guys. We all bring something different to the table and I’m really excited for the partnership. With the official Grand opening this weekend I hope everyone can start coming out to ride and enjoy what we have created here. We came together with a common goal- Making a place all ages and levels can have fun riding! Load up the bikes - let’s go 🤙🏽

Man 2009 was a fun year!
After SX I went back to Australia for some time off as I only had a SX only contract 
Got bored and missed my badass team and bike so decided to race MX after two years off😅😤
It was a grind to get back up to speed, but I was excited to find a feeling outdoors that I’d always been chasing . 
09 was so good. learned so much, wish it lasted into 2010 and beyond. 
The great outdoors is now streaming for the first time ever @tgomotocross check it out! 
@mrstwotwo @thereal_goose @slasher200

node.text:
Today was one for the books! 😂
Stories that’ll bring some laughs for years to come,I had a blast with the boys going trail riding.
I grew up having access to the bush 🇦🇺 (woods) 🇺🇸 and spent hours riding and getting lost -it’s always half the fun. 
In all my crazy shenanigans over the years I’ve never ran out of options where I had to cross a river 😂 ✅ 
Very limited options today 
We tried climbing back out but it was 400 meters straight up and impossible to make it out
@kr_557 made the call that we weren’t going to be able to make it back up!
Side note it was his choice of trail that got us stuck in the first place but I somehow still trusted him 😅 
So back to the bottom it was 🤷🏽‍♂️
This video makes me laugh so hard -man I love motorcycles !
Luckily Ive been watching running wild with @beargrylls 🤙🏾 
What a day boys. 
@justinp_21_  @sheetmetal220 @layne523 @gatlin_welborn17 @mountainmotorsports_

Who remembers that feeling of heading down to the start line for your first race/practice?
Unfortunately I can’t, but the feeling never really changed, so I feel like I have a pretty good idea of how it felt. 😍
Lots of amazing memories flooded my mind yesterday, watching all 3 kids experience moto racing for their first time as the racers..
Funny that it felt normal🤷🏽‍♂️ 
I’ve been so far removed from 2 stroke smoke damn! Those 65-85 starts are brutal !
😂💨😷
